.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-23 long\-form content (articles and drafts). Articles are
kind 30023 addressable events with Markdown content and optional metadata
tags. Drafts are kind 30024 with the same structure.
.PP
Content should be Markdown text. Clients creating articles MUST NOT hard
line\-break paragraphs and MUST NOT include HTML in the Markdown.
.PP
Articles are editable via the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag identifier. The \f(CW\*(C`created_at\*(C'\fR field
represents the date of the last update. Use the \f(CW\*(C`published_at\*(C'\fR tag for the
original publication date.
.PP
References to other Nostr entities in the content should use \f(CW\*(C`nostr:\*(C'\fR URIs
(NIP\-21).
.PP
Replies to articles MUST use NIP\-22 kind 1111 comments (see
Net::Nostr::Comment).
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Article\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Article\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Article\->new(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-article\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqMy Article\*(Aq,
\&        summary    => \*(AqA brief overview.\*(Aq,
\&        image      => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/cover.jpg\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`title\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`image\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`summary\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`published_at\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR). Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS article
.IX Subsection "article"
.Vb 12
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Article\->article(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,         # required
\&        content      => $markdown,          # required
\&        identifier   => \*(Aqarticle\-slug\*(Aq,     # required (d tag)
\&        title        => \*(AqArticle Title\*(Aq,    # optional
\&        image        => \*(Aqhttps://...\*(Aq,      # optional
\&        summary      => \*(AqShort summary.\*(Aq,   # optional
\&        published_at => 1296962229,         # optional (unix timestamp)
\&        hashtags     => [\*(Aqtopic1\*(Aq],         # optional (t tags)
\&        extra_tags   => [[\*(Aqe\*(Aq, $id, $r]],   # optional (additional tags)
\&        created_at   => time(),             # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30023 article Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR,
and \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR are required. All metadata fields are optional.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`published_at\*(C'\fR value is stringified in the tag per spec. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`extra_tags\*(C'\fR parameter accepts an arrayref of additional tags (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags for references).
.PP
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Article\->article(
\&        pubkey     => \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32,
\&        content    => "# Hello\en\enWorld.",
\&        identifier => \*(Aqhello\-world\*(Aq,
\&        title      => \*(AqHello\*(Aq,
\&        hashtags   => [\*(Aqgreeting\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.SS draft
.IX Subsection "draft"
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Article\->draft(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content    => $markdown,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqdraft\-slug\*(Aq,
\&        # same optional params as article()
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30024 draft event. Accepts the same parameters as
"article". Drafts have the same structure as articles but are not
intended for publication.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Article\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses article metadata from a kind 30023 or 30024 Net::Nostr::Event.
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Article\*(C'\fR object with accessors, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the
event is not an article or draft kind.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Article\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->identifier;   # \*(Aqmy\-article\*(Aq
\&    say $info\->title;        # \*(AqMy Article\*(Aq or undef
\&    say $info\->hashtags;     # [\*(Aqnostr\*(Aq, \*(Aqblog\*(Aq]
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Article\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-23 article. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 30023 or 30024
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::Article\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid article: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SS to_naddr
.IX Subsection "to_naddr"
.Vb 3
\&    my $naddr = Net::Nostr::Article\->to_naddr($event,
\&        relays => [\*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Generates a NIP\-19 \f(CW\*(C`naddr\*(C'\fR bech32 string for linking to the article.
The \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR parameter is optional.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $naddr = Net::Nostr::Article\->to_naddr($article_event);
\&    # naddr1...
.Ve
